Here's a small header-only helper:

```cpp
#include <string>
#include <string_view>

[[nodiscard]] inline std::string reverse_string(std::string_view in) {
    return std::string(in.rbegin(), in.rend());
}
```

It constructs the result directly from reverse iterators, so it also handles **empty** and single-character inputs without special cases.
